ages/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tejaye>Tejaye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 8:46:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   When on a Horse, are you Medding 100% of the Time?</span><hr size=1> I was curious when on Horse, are you always medding?<br>
I heard from some you med when standing still as long as you are not casting/running/fighting(melee)?<br>
Or are you medding 100% of the time regardless of what you are doing? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2426<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 9:14:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When on a Horse, are you Medding 100% of the Time?</span><hr size=1> Many threads on this, especially in the EQUIPMENT FORUM.<br>
<br>
Short answer: if you are neither moving nor attacking, then you are considered meditating.  This definitely includes during the cast of right clicks, and apparently also includes during normal spell casts.  As soon as you move or attack, you are no longer medding.<br>
<br>
This is to the best of my knowledge based on experience and reading.<br>
<br>
