 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=turzem>Turzem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 9:40:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~yolora/personal.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When on a Horse, are you Medding 100% of the Time?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>As soon as you move or attack, you are no longer medding.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Wrong.<br>
<br>
