<br>
Moving around, casting spells, clicking items, whatever, you are still medding.  <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:perpetua;font-size:x-small;">Turzem Setanta -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=421973">Arch Mage</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net">Insidious Blood</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1168<br> <font color=#333333>(12/1/02 9:51:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: When on a Horse, are you Medding 100% of the Time?</span><hr size=1> Easy way to check.. Go down to a predetermined number of mana like 50%.. See how long it takes you to med to 100% with a horse just sitting there, then get a real long casting time click item (or a short one if you like clicking a lot) and cast it at 50% - 100% ..<br>
