the only way i see them as usuful is if you have a rt. click nuke item. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zarc22>Zarc22</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 1:46:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: ..</span><hr size=1> Horses also make life easier if you're a frequent user of bolt spells (like the lvl 61 2k bolt). Getting that high viewpoint you are more likely to get a clear line of sight to your target while group/raid melees are beating up the mob. Might not be that much an advantage for small races (I'm Erudite). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hurk>Hurk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 1:48:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  horse</span><hr size=1> 1. you regain mana whenever not moving  (turning in place doesnt count) and when auto attack is off.<br>
<br>
2. being on a horse counts as standing for agro perpuses.  mobs that would only attack you while sitting will not attack you while on horse.  mobs that attack you while standing will still attack you.<br>
<br>
3. horse regen works even when casting spells, so its always on meditation for most caster classes.  it easily pays for itself in saved time.  horses are a must for dual boxed characters. (my wizard increased efficiantcy about 40%) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ylaine76>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1169<br> <font color=#333333>(12/2/02 3:54:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8017.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: horse</span><hr size=1> Yeah just tested myself, took me 2mins 50 seconds to go from 80m to FM with no mana buffs on and no casting.  Took me basically the same amount of time chain casting a 15 second right click <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/YlaineEQ/fullsize/cheersig2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
